 _______________________________________________________________________

 Mandriva Linux Security Advisory                         MDVSA-2014:173
 http://www.mandriva.com/en/support/security/
 _______________________________________________________________________

 Package : busybox
 Date    : September 3, 2014
 Affected: Business Server 1.0
 _______________________________________________________________________

 Problem Description:

 Updated busybox packages fix security vulnerability:
 
 An integer overflow in liblzo before 2.07 allows attackers to cause
 a denial of service or possibly code execution in applications using
 performing LZO decompression on a compressed payload from the attacker
 (CVE-2014-4607).
 
 Busybox bundles part of the liblzo code, containing the
 lzo1x_decompress_safe function, which is affected by this issue.
 _______________________________________________________________________

 References:

 http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2014-4607
 http://advisories.mageia.org/MGASA-2014-0351.html
 _______________________________________________________________________

